cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with visual recognition tasks and proposes a generalized discriminative latent model for such tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses a framework for learning the model, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with latent variables, which could place it in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses scoring functions, which could place it in the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper experiments with Deformable Part Models, which could place it in the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
